plot: Dee embraces the desperate, self-loathing qualities the guys have beaten her into over the years, sending her stand-up comedy to unexpected places.

After the gang starts noticing that Dee is depressed and most likely suicidal, they decide to sign her up for a stand up comedy show to raise her mood. But then after a successful show, Dee starts to gain her self-esteem back and show by show, slowly leaves the gang including leaving Dennis out of his place.—James Hake
